{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nOnly Claude Code (remote) and OpenCode actually expose a readable session env var; Codex\nexplicitly does NOT (no supported programmatic access), and Cursor has none yet. So beyond\nClaude Code + OpenCode, the portable `REBAR_SESSION_ID` must be populated by each harness's\nown lifecycle mechanism, or the feature no-ops there. This story ships copy-paste capture\nshims for Codex and Cursor.\n\n## What\n- **Codex** SessionStart hook (Codex has its own hooks) exports `REBAR_SESSION_ID` (derived\n  from the `~/.codex/sessions/` rollout id, or a generated id) AND the harness-provenance tag\n  `AI_AGENT=codex` (consumed by story c557's `claim_harness`).\n- **Cursor** `.cursor/environment.json` start-script snippet exports `REBAR_SESSION_ID` for\n  cloud agents (and a local shell/tmux note) AND `AI_AGENT=cursor`.\n- Per-harness install docs.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the Codex hook + Cursor start-script snippet (each exporting `REBAR_SESSION_ID` +\n  `AI_AGENT`) and per-harness install docs.\n- OUT: Gemini CLI / other harnesses (follow-up); the record/read core (S1-S3, S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Codex SessionStart hook exports `REBAR_SESSION_ID` and `AI_AGENT=codex`; a Codex claim\n      records `claimed_session` and `claim_harness`.\n- [ ] Cursor start-script snippet exports `REBAR_SESSION_ID` and `AI_AGENT=cursor`; a\n      Cursor-agent claim records them.\n- [ ] Per-harness install docs shipped.\n\n## Depends on\n- S5 (the resolver + `AI_AGENT` -> `claim_harness` record path)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783545979621383001,"uuid":"3856adf1-3d88-4d80-9c65-3b1fd082c4e1"}